(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:1.0em;&amp;#34; %)**Xu et al 12**(%%) (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:0.8em;&amp;#34; %)(Ting, with Thieß Petersen and Tianlong Wang, Cash in Hand: Chinese Foreign Direct Investment in the U.S. and Germany, June, http:~/~/www.bfna.org/sites/default/files/publications/Cash%20In%20Hand.pdf)


(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in; &amp;#34; %)
Many U.S. experts recognize the potentially enormous future benefit from growing Chinese

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in; &amp;#34; %)
AND

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in; &amp;#34; %)
welcome Chinese investment and in particular, to treat the SOEs equally. 4


(% class=&amp;#34;western&amp;#34; %)
=== Plan ===

(% class=&amp;#34;western&amp;#34; %)
==== Thus the plan: ====

(% class=&amp;#34;western&amp;#34; %)
==== The United States Federal Government should exclude crude oil and natural gas production from Exon-Florio reviews. ====



